  "body": "This is a minor issue, but I thought I'd document it. It feels a lot worse than it is I'm sure.\r\n\r\nWhen shutting down, TG responds to the control+C, but then says \"Ethereum peer registration failed\" which sound ominous. It further says \"Looking for peers\" which is also seems ominous.\r\n\r\nPerhaps it would be better if, once TG knows it's shutting down, it no longer reports that it's trying to connect to peers.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5417918/100681789-878db000-3342-11eb-9f39-e56acd2fd793.png)\r\n",
